Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips
(no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Sprinkle with the @Mexican style spice
mix{1%sachet}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the @garlic{3%cloves}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with
a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it. Roast the parcel until soft,
~{10-12%minutes}.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice. Cut the
@medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks. Cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

In a large #bowl{}, combine half the lime juice with the @sugar{1%tsp} and
@olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the
skin and mash with a #fork{}.

In a small bowl, combine the roasted garlic with the @Greek style natural
yoghurt{75%g} and @chipotle paste{20%g}. Set aside.

> Add less chipotle paste if you'd prefer things milder.

When the chips are nearly ready, put a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add
enough @olive oil{} to completely coat the bottom of the pan.

Once hot, carefully add the @ready to eat falafels{171%g} to the pan and reduce
the heat to medium-high. Cook until golden, ~{2-4%minutes}. Adjust the heat as
necessary.

Pop the @plain taco tortillas{4} (2 per person) into the oven to warm through,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the falafels are cooked, slice them in half.

Add the lettuce and tomato to the bowl of lime dressing. Toss to evenly coat.

Top your tortillas with the baby gem & tomato salad, followed by the falafels.
Spoon over the chipotle yoghurt and crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g}.

Serve with the chips on the side with the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} for dipping.

> Enjoy!